            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38699",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As described in the manual, using the mimetype which is sent from the client is very unsecure.\r\n\r\nFor security reasons the clients mimetype will never be used.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-23T14:46:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-23T14:46:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38705",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=souldude",
                        "name": "souldude",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Straakenbroek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for the reply, i'll ask the host if they will install the fileinfo package",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=souldude",
                        "name": "souldude",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Straakenbroek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-24T01:13:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-24T01:13:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38722",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When you really want to get unsecure you could store the mimetype your client set before any model is invoked and work with this mimetype.\r\n\r\nBut, as noted before, ZF methods will not use this value for security reasons. Even the Mimetype Validator will not use your value, but the real found mimetype.\r\n\r\nIn this case you would have to extend the classes you want to use (Zend_File, Zend_Validate, Zend_Filter and so on...) and add this unsecure behaviour in userland.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nThis is workflow you should prevent in any case when there is a possibility for you.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-24T10:47:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-24T10:47:52.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
